title.original: Mazunte Oaxaca Pueblo Mágico y sus hermosas playas

description.original:
Mazunte es una de las playas más bonitas y poco conocidas de Oaxaca. El primer día que despiertes aquí te recibirá un cielo azul, un clima caluroso y el sonido del suave oleaje.

Por la tarde un cielo anaranjando te invitará a la contemplación y relajarte, lo cual es cada vez menos frecuente en otras playas mexicanas. La gente es amable, cualquiera te puede dar pistas de cómo pasartela bien.

Para que te enamores más de Mazunte te presentamos algunos de sus mejores lugares para visitar.

1. Punta cometa

En el extremo occidental de la bahía Mazunte se forma una media luna conocida como Punta Cometa, no solo te recomendamos que vayas a este lugar por tener acceso a algunos de los mejores amaneceres de la costa sino también porque al lugar se le considera un  lugar cósmico y energético. 

2.  Centro Mexicano de la Tortuga

Aunque no lo creas Mazunte no siempre fue el paraíso que hoy conocemos, antes era el rastro tortuguero más grande de México, hasta 1990 cuando el gobierno prohibió esta práctica. El Centro Mexicano de la Tortuga, ubicado en Mazunte, te permite colaborar con ellos en el rescate de estos reptiles con voluntariados de mínimo un mes. 

3. Come en la Estrella Fugaz

Es considerado uno de los mejores lugares para comer en Mazunte, es admirado por sus cafés, desayunos riquísimos. Tienen un pequeño local llamado Kapricho, especilizado en ofrecer ceviches, ensalsadas y sandwiches.

4. Practíca Skimboard

Para los que practican los deportes acuáticos Mazunte es especial por la forma en que aquí rompen las olas. Atrévete a subirte a una tabla de skimboarding, una tabla más corta y ancha que las de surf. Para realizar esta actividad pregunta en dónde está el Mazunteskim, ellos te orientarán.

5. Avistamiento de ballenas jorobadas

Si tienes planeado visitar este paraíso oaxaqueño en un futuro cercano te recomendamos que lo hagas entre diciembre y marzo. Durante está temporada las ballenas jorobadas migran por las playas de Mazunte. Por lo que puedes admirar de este espectacular animal desde Cerro Sagrado.

Pisar la dorada arena de Mazunte, mientras el mantra de sus olas te arrulla con su vaivén de suave tonalidad turquesa será como caer un paraíso.

En Mazunte tus días transcurrirán lentamente. Te contagiarás de la pasividad del oleaje que pareciera no tener prisa para alcanzar la orilla de la playa, o del sol que calmo atraviesa el cielo hasta el atardecer; cuando la oscuridad llega muy lentamente parece que se despierta la poesía visual a su paso pues mientras la noche cae el radiante naranja del sol se oculta y comienzan a salir los grillos para acompañarlo con su canto; es una dulzura que casi podrás tocar. Los únicos testigos serán tú y las tortugas que regresan a casa.

title.original: SECRET COVE - Nanjizal Bay, Nr Lands End, Cornwall

description.original:
Inspired by photos on Instagram of a stunning rock formation and a book called Secret Cornwall, we set out to find Nanjizal Bay. 

Joins us as we walk through farmland and tracks to reach this special cove, litter with pebble the size of dinosaur eggs and a scramble over some hefty rocks, we eventually reach the marvel, the Song of the Sea.

This walk, is a there and back walk. We park in Trevescan, a little hamlet near Lands End, walk via footpaths down to Nanjizal Bay. This walk in total is just over 2 miles.

For an annotated video and written walk instructions, please join us on Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/Cornishwalkingtrails

title.original: Gray Whale Trio Migrates With Dolphin Companions | Capt. Dave's Dana Point Whale Watching

description.original:
#whales #danapoint #captdaves

Three migrating gray whales seem to enjoy each other's company, and that of their common dolphin companions, in this drone video filmed off the coast of Dana Point, California, in March 2019.

Gray whales make one of the longest migrations of any mammal. Traveling every year along the U.S. West Coast from their feeding grounds north of Alaska to their mating and birthing lagoons in Baja California, Mexico. Once called "devil fish" by whale hunters, gray whales are now known as the "friendly whale", thanks to their amiable behavior towards boats and the inclination to bring their calves over to be touched by humans in the protected lagoons.

title.original: Adventure Ocean Quest: The Giants of Rurutu | Free Documentary Nature

description.original:
Humpback whales are amongst the biggest known mammals on Earth, weighing in at around 36.000kg, but by the early 1960s, after 34 million years on this planet, these gentle, majestic giants had been hunted almost to extinction. With their populations now in partial recovery, it is once again possible to find humpback whales around Rurutu in Polynesian waters. They congregate here between July and November to give birth to a new generation, and to mate. The newborns are prepared for a life of migration, covering thousands of kilometres every single year.

စတီဗင်ဟော့ကင်းဟာ သီအိုရီ ရူပဗဒေပညာရှငျ နဲ့ နက်ခတ်တဗဒေပညာရှငျတဈယောကျ ဖြစ်ပါတယ် 
 
ဇန်နာဝါရီလ ၈ ရက် ၁၉၄၂ ခုနှစ် အော့စဖို့မြို့ ( oxford ) အင်္ဂလန်မှာ မွေးဖွားခဲ့ပါတယ်  

ဖခင်တော့ ဖရန့်ဟော့ကင်း( frank hawking) ဖြစ်ပြီးမိခင်ကတော့ အိုင်ဆိုဘယ်ဟော့ကင်း( isobal hawking) ပါ

ဖခင်ကတော့ ဆေးဘက်ဆိုင်ရာသုသေသနပညာရှင်( medical researcher) ဲဖြစ်ပြီးမိခင်ကတော့ အောက်စဖို့တက္ကသိုလ်က  နေ ပထမဆုံး ဘွဲ့ရခဲ့တဲ့ အမျိုးသမီးတွေထဲက တစ်ယောက်ဖြစ်ပါတယ်

description.original:
ボクハワEP9は朝食を食べた後からスタート！
トイレを探しにマサ＆ジョイスオカズヤ近くのショッピングセンター「ウインドワードシティショッピングセンター」へ行きました。
そこにあったロングスドラッグスが朝7時から営業していたので、ロングスでトイレを探しました。そしたら意外な所を案内され・・。
その後行ったホオマルヒアボタアニカルガーデンは、美しい緑と花の宝庫でした。どうぞご覧ください！

2019.10.23～30　11回目のハワイ旅行へ6泊8日で行ってまいりました。
今年もレンタカーでオアフ島ローカルエリアを走り回り　★美味しいもの　★綺麗な景色　をたくさん食べて・見てきました。
今回のシリーズも長ーく続きますので、是非チャンネル登録をお願いします！！

●インスタグラムはこちら！
　https://www.instagram.com/alphasensecomplete/

　軽キャン・ハワイ・音楽・プライベート　などの写真をアップしてます。

【ボクハワ的ハワイ旅行のスタイル】

　ローカルエリアをレンタカーで巡る旅。早朝からワイキキエリアを飛び出して、オアフ島のいろんなローカルエリアへ行き、ガイドブックには載っていない場所やグルメを自己流で探す。そして夜には寝るためにワイキキのホテルに戻る。そんな旅のスタイルです。日本人観光客の少ないエリアを旅するため、ブランドショップなどは全くと言っていいほど出てきません（笑）そして私たちは英語がほぼ喋れません。それなのに日本語がほぼ通じないエリアへと行くので、いつも「言葉の壁」にぶち当たります。でもハワイの人は優しい方が多いので「ハワイ好きの日本人観光客」の私たちにいつも親切にしてくれます。僕はそんなハワイが大好きです。

　何回かハワイへ行ったことがあるけど「もう少し自由にハワイを旅してみたい」・・そんなふうに考えている方へ、この動画が少しでも参考になったり、また初めてハワイへ行く方へは、動画の中に出てくるたくさんの美しいスポットを見て、ハワイ旅行へ行くきっかけになったら嬉しいです。そんな私もまだまだハワイの知らない場所がたくさんありますけど（笑）。
僕はたぶん一生ハワイに通い続けるでしょう！
みなさまののコメントお待ちしております！

title.original: Wave Of The Day: Pipeline

description.original:
South Carolina goofyfoot vagabond Cam Richards is no stranger to wild, bucking bronco waves at Pipeline, as evidenced by last year's O'Neill Wave of the Winter contender. And on opening day at Pipe this past Monday, he managed an eerily similar ride.

“It was a pretty bumpy morning,” he said. “Not too good, but you could tell there was a few — and not too crowded. So it was a good time to get out there, especially with it being the first Pipe swell. I had a bunch of bad ones before, and swung at that one last-minute — it didn’t look too good, and then I almost ate it on the drop. And then I recovered and did one big pump and it spit and I was blind for the whole wave, just waiting to get lipped in the head. And then it cleared up, and I was lucky enough to doggy door. It was super fun and looking forward to the rest of the season. Couldn’t ask for a better start.”

Surfer: Cam Richards
Video: Nate Neal

title.original: Was that a dolphin I saw in Puget Sound?

description.original:
A few species of animals can look a lot like dolphins, especially from a distance. Video clips and information about distinguishing features of harbor porpoise, common dolphins, bottlenose dolphins,  Dall's porpoise, Pacific white-sided dolphins, and killer whales are featured in this video. Many of these species, except for harbor porpoise and killer whales, are not commonly seen in Puget Sound and researchers would like to learn more about the presence and behavior of these animals.  Please contact Cascadia Research to report sightings of unusual marine mammal species. http://www.cascadiaresearch.org/

title.original: Ep 163 | Signs, Flag, Clutch Fix, Final Preparations for Tonga Departure, Sailing South Pacific

description.original:
We start to make preparations for leaving the Kingdom of Tonga to sail to Norfolk Island via the beautiful Minerva Reef. We’ve heard that the crayfish are fabulous on the south reef so we’re going to check it out.

We pick up a few last minute food supplies and do the final boat jobs that need to be done for the next passage.

Magnus finally manages to fix the problem which is causing Izzy, the engine, to continually fill up with salt water! The autopilot clutch is fixed, yet again. We’re hoping it will make it all the way to Australia. The sails get a few stitches, hatches get resealed and Nutshell gets a big tidy up.

We know that Australia is very strict with quarantine when entering, so give Nutshell a good clean and clear out unwanted and not needed items, in preparation for Australian customs.

Wendy makes a new courtesy flag for our Norfolk Island arrival.

Oh, and we show you how convoluted the process is for finding customs to check out of Tonga!

Thanks for watching and following along with our adventures.

Wendy and Magnus

title.original: 星空と流れ星ライブ2019/08/30

description.original:
朝日新聞社と東京大学の天文台がコラボし、星空ライブを始めました。

ペルセウス座流星群はほぼ終わりましたが、ここ木曽の夜空ならいつも１０分で一つくらいは流れ星が見られます。

ライブカメラが写しているのは北東の空。この時期はカシオペア座やペルセウス座が見えます。天候にかかわらず配信しますので、曇っちゃったらごめんなさい。

協力：東京大学大学院理学系研究科附属天文学教育研究センター木曽観測所（長野県木曽郡）。ドームにあるのはシュミット式で世界最大級の「105cmシュミット望遠鏡」。最新の動画カメラ「トモエゴゼン（Tomo-e Gozen）」を装備して試験観測中です。

ライブカメラの画角は左右70度、上下50度。16mmF1.4、ISO100-204800

title.original: Seal freed from fishing net around her neck - successful animal rescue

original: Baby seal with a big fishing hook

description.original: Ninja stealth mode. Due to it being pup season, I need to be really cautious about disturbance in the colonies. I spent the last few days developing some tools for a new technique. As the seals don’t have great eyesight, I found a large female with some netting gagging her and looped around the back of her head. It tools about 10 minutes of slow crawling to infiltrate the group and I got about 2 meters away without causing disturbance. The video doesn’t give justice to the size of the Bull that came to check me out and made me feel real small and vulnerable.... Obviously I didn’t have the luxury of removing the whole entanglement, but with it being cut the tension is off, which is instant pain relief, and it will surely fall off soon as she splashes around in the water again.

title.original: Canada - Newfoundland and Labrador - Beautiful views.

description.original:
Newfoundland and Labrador form the most easterly province of Canada. On Newfoundland island, the Norse archaeological site L'Anse aux Meadows is the reputed settlement of Viking explorer Leif Erikson. Gros Morne National Park, on the Gulf of St Lawrence, has cliffs, waterfalls and glacial fjords. Southeastern capital city St. John’s is known for the 17th-century Signal Hill citadel, with a hillside walking trail.
Population: 521,542 (2019) 
Capital: St. John's
Newfoundland and Labrador, the journey can be as colourful as stories told around the kitchen table. As meandering as our thousands of kilometres of coastline. As surprising as a humpback whale breaching in the mist. Or as comforting as bakeapple jam. There are places that travel with you, wherever you go.
Visit : https://www.newfoundlandlabrador.com/

#Canada #NewfoundandandLabrado #Beautyplace

title.original: Coronavirus (Covid-19) Fin Whales reclaim waters (French Coast) - ITV News - 9th April 2020

original: Coronavirus (Covid-19) Fin Whales reclaim waters (French Coast) - ITV News - 9th April 2020

description.original:
Off Marseille (French coast), a couple of Fin whales have been spotted reclaiming waters that are not so busy with international shipping dramatically reduced. I have been wondering how much the air and other areas will reduce in pollution as we have already seen animals entering towns and cities that are devoid of humans the three days of air grounding after 9/11 (in 2001) cleared up the air dramatically, could something happen again here with reduced air travel? Scientists will have a perfect opportunity to observe all this and more at this time. We shall have to wait and see. They will avoid it once the world economy gears up again, no doubt.

description.original:
Releasing stress through the facility of Meditation Relaxing Music:
Music can have a profound effect on both the emotions and therefore the body. Faster music can cause you to feel more alert and concentrate better. Current findings indicate that music around 60 beats per minute can cause the brain to synchronize with the beat causing alpha brainwaves (frequencies from 8 - 14 hertz or cycles per second). 

This alpha brainwave is what's present once we are relaxed and conscious. To induce sleep (a delta brainwave of 5 hertz), an individual may have to devote a minimum of 45 minutes, during a relaxed position, taking note of calming music.

 Researchers at Stanford University have said that "listening to music seems to be ready to change brain functioning to an equivalent extent as medication." They noted that music is some things that nearly anybody can access and makes it a simple stress reduction tool.

So what sort of music reduces stress the best? A touch surprising is that Native American, Celtic, Indian stringed-instruments, drums, and flutes are very effective at relaxing the mind even when played moderately loud. 

Sounds of rain, thunder, and nature sounds also can be relaxing particularly when mixed with other music, like light jazz, classical (the "largo" movement), and easy listening music. 

Since with music we are rarely told the beats per minute, how does one choose the relief music that's best for you? The solution partly rests with you: you want to first just like the music being played, and then it must relax you. 

You’ll start by simply exploring the music on this website. Some may relax you, some might not. Forcing yourself to concentrate to relaxation music that irritates you'll create tension, not reduce it.

title.original: Djuma Private Game Reserve Live Stream

description.original:
This camera watches over Gowrie dam on Djuma Game Reserve, in the Sabi Sand Wildtuin, South Africa. In fact this is the oldest waterhole cam in Africa and the world. It’s been broadcasting LIVE from this spot since 1998. With some luck you will see big cats coming for a drink o even on a kill close by. You can also expect to see a lot of impala (light brown antelope), waterbuck (white circle on rump), nyala (males have yellow legs and females have white stripes on flanks) and many other types of mammals, birds and reptiles.

The camera is remotely controlled by a volunteer corps of people around the world known as ‘zoomies’. They log into the camera according to a schedule in shifts, and pan, tilt and zoom in search of animals. They also Tweet sightings @WildEarth Djuma was started almost twenty years ago as a safari, lodge by the Moolman family, and is renowned for the quality of its game safaris.

title.original: [Eng Sub]세계 최고의 포식자 범고래이야기 Killer Whale story  'Free Willy'

description.original:
Killer whales are the best predators that dominate the world's oceans.
Not only in strength, but in intelligence, it overwhelms almost all animals.
The male adult is 9.8meters and weighs 10 tons.
Do you remember the movie, Free Willy, with this killer whale as its main character?
Killer whales are unlikely to be tamed by humans.
Shamu is performing at SeaWorld in San Antonio, USA
This is Sea World's mascot.
Shall we watch Shamu's show "Once one" at SeaWorld?

Shamu is the nickname for killer whales at Sea World.
SeaWorld has been criticized by animal lovers.
Because they are taming killer whales for the show.
The killer whale called Geiko, the protagonist of the movie Free Willy
went back to the sea again.
Geiko, who has become accustomed to the care of people,
Unfortunately, died from hunger and pneumonia.
If it hadn't been tamed by human hands from the beginning
it would have been free to swim in the sea and live happily with the crowd.
Nowadays, we realize that humans and nature must coexist.

title.original: Ft. Worth, Texas USA | Cam of the Week - Virtual Railfan LIVE

description.original:
Started streaming on June 26, 2017

Welcome to Virtual Railfan, please read the important info below.

You are watching a live stream of Tower 55 in Fort Worth, Texas, for people who enjoy watching trains. You are welcome to join our family friendly chat, but keep in mind that there’s a community with rules already established.  Please check them out. 

Duplication or distribution of our videos is strictly prohibited without permission.

CHAT RULES:

• Be polite and respectful
• Use English, we need a single language to be able to understand each other. If you’re not fluent, please use a translator such as Google Translate.
• Don’t post in ALL CAPS or use excessive emojis.
• Don’t discuss politics, religion, race, sex, violence, train or vehicle accidents, or anything like that. We try to be mindful of any children who may be watching. 
• The conversation here is trains, and please remember that said on topic conversation needs to come first. Off topic conversation such as music, sports, jokes, etc. is fine, but it must be kept in balance with on topic.
• Please keep conversations of personal issues (medical, domestic, legal, etc.) out of the chat; take it to messaging or email. Remember, you are sharing information with hundreds of people, not just those directly involved in the chat.
• Don’t ask to become a moderator. It’s earned. If we’re interested in your assistance, we will contact you.
• Just be nice, it’s amazing what happens when we’re all nice to each other.

THINGS THAT WILL GET YOU BANNED: 

• Inappropriate usernames
• Profanity
• Asking for subscriptions (subs)
• Being intentionally disruptive, creating arguments or any other jerk-like behavior 
• Not following the moderators’ instructions 

ABOUT THIS FEED:

Tower 55 is located in Fort Worth, Texas. The camera is the SW quadrant of the crossing, mounted on the NE corner of the Morrison Supply Company. There are more than 100 freight trains that travel through here a day - UP, BNSF and FWWR. Amtrak runs two trains daily that pass through here, #21 & 22, the Texas Eagle. You can see the Trinity Railway Express (TRE) line in the background as well.

When’s the next train? Yeah, we get this a lot. You can figure out the next Amtrak passenger train with this handy link: https://bit.ly/2M4bFLF

There’s no schedule for freight trains, but some of our more knowledgeable members will provide real-time information when it’s available. Please refrain from asking.

ABOUT VIRTUAL RAILFAN:

Virtual Railfan currently has nearly 50 cams from 3 countries. Visit our website for memberships, more free cams, and our own live chat. Thanks for stopping by, we’re glad you’re here! 

Website: http://virtualrailfan.com 
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/virtualrailfan/ 
Twitter: https://twitter.com/virtual_railfan 

Know a good location for a camera? We’d love to hear! Please email us at sales@virtualrailfan.com. If you have any contacts in the area, please let us know.

title.original: Why Bitcoin Whales are Mass-Dumping Before Crypto’s Big Halving

description.original:
Please change your life!!! Click on the link! http://youtube.com+watch=@3162039724/IaBL
Can you afford this thing?: http://youtube.com+watch=@3162039724/orwTH
Software at the best prices: http://amzn.com@3162039724/f3ANs

In less than 10 hours, the highly anticipated Bitcoin halving will be activated. But, whales seem to be taking the opportunity to dump on the market. Since Friday, bitcoin price dropped by more than 14% from $10,020 to $8,550. At its lowest point on May 10, it reached $8,100, marking a 20% decline ahead of the halving. The Bitcoin blockchain network is primarily divided into three groups: developers, users, and miners. Miners verify blocks that contain payment data using electricity and mining equipment such as high-power computing chips. When a miner verifies a block and the block then enters the Bitcoin blockchain, the miner is compensated with BTC. When the block reward halving occurs, which happens every four years, it decreases the compensation miners receive by half. Prior to the 2020 halving, Bitcoin miners earned around 1,800 BTC every day. Post-halving, miners are expected to generate around 900 BTC per day. Bitcoin is a deflationary currency because of its fixed supply of 21 million BTC. As such, any occurrence that affects the supply of BTC will inevitably have a significant impact on its long-term price trend. In theory, the halving is likely to have a positive effect on the price of Bitcoin over the next four years. Less BTC will be mined by miners, which means less BTC will be sold to the market. But, as seen in the 2016 halving, the Bitcoin price tends to drop right before and after a halving occurs. A post-halving drop happens as whales move to take advantage of rising retail demand. In April, data shows that spot volume of Bitcoin rose noticeably on platforms like Coinbase and Binance. Hence, heading into the halving, the demand for Bitcoin from retail investors is higher than in previous months. For whales, this means liquidity. Whales that hold millions of dollars worth of Bitcoin cannot sell BTC when they do not see much buying demand in the market. Whales typically wait for BTC price to rise to a local high point, and then initiate a sell-off. It is for this reason that the Bitcoin price sees a large shift in trend and a predictable cycle. In the past three months, the Bitcoin price increased from $3,600 to $10,065, by nearly three-fold. Most of the buying demand came from spot exchanges that saw record high volume in late April. Whales that accumulated in the $3,000 to $4,000 range have the incentive to sell at $10,000 where there is high liquidity and retail demand. The high price also coincided with a positive narrative in halving, similar to October 2019 when Chinese President Xi Jinping encouraged the development of blockchain technology. At the time, the Bitcoin price abruptly rose from $7,700 to $10,500 within a 48-hour span. Given that Bitcoin trading remains prohibited in China, it is difficult to state that a fear of missing out (FOMO) hit the Chinese market and retail investors bought in.

title.original: Whale-watching in the St Lawrence River's salt water

description.original:
Salt water and tides continue up-river within the St. Lawrence as far as Quebec City.  An exciting intersection of waters on the way upstream from the Atlantic Ocean to this provincial capital occurs as the Saguenay river triumphs through a dramatic fjord into the St. Lawrence.  
Six different varieties of whales are seen regularly at this junction, as well as seals and sea birds.  We hope to encounter whales from the water-level perzpective of a zodiac with just 6 passengers on this occasion.
AND WE DO~!  You'll see some coming up to greet us.
The Essipit native peoples run this outfit from Les Bergeronnes, Quebec...
Check out this experience.  In nature, nothing is predictable, but as our helmsman said:  "We had a GIFT."  So, we share an up close and personal greeting from humpback whales.

title.original: Ten Awesome Adventures Los Cabos 2020, Cabo Activities, Cabo Yacht charters

description.original:
Ten Awesome Adventures in Los Cabos
https://www.cabosfinest.com/blog-2/
First up we have something for everyone at Wild Canyon Adventures.
Wild Canyon is an adventure park located in the tourist corridor of Cabo San Lucas – San José del Cabo where you will find many activities and extreme sports. Within this huge adventure park, you will find the longest monster zip-lining in Baja! They also have “La Gondola” a funicular unique in its style with glass floors where you bungee jump and giant swing 300 feet above the ground. They have so many ways to play including off-roading tours, camel rides, moon zipping, and their new water park. The longest suspension bridge will also get your adrenaline pumping. Wild Canyon offers different combo packages and restaurant and bar.

Combo Horseback & ATV tour at Rancho Carisuva-
For over a decade Rancho Carisuva has hosted international guests to their oceanfront eco-park. They offer authentic ecological outdoor adventures just north of Cabo. The dedication to the animals is apparent as soon as you arrive in one of their air-conditioned vans. These happy horses, burros, and farm animals are friendly and smile at you while touring you through their amazing property. The combination of horseback and ATV tour is their most popular. You will spend the day discovering the Baja like it used to be. You will leave feeling satisfied that your contribution is directly used to maintain their well cared for animals, ranch, and help preserve the traditions of the magical land.

Book a Private Charter on Zigzag Catamaran.
Zig Zag is known in Cabo as the most luxurious sailing catamaran. Elegance and service along with great food and water toys make this a great way to spend a day on the ocean and Sea. They have 9 years of experience receiving groups from the most prestigious resorts. Their priority is to create a one of a kind customer experience so the guests can remember it as the highlight of their trip. How about sailing in the most extraordinary sunsets in Cabo? Your options are plenty with kayaks, SUP, snorkeling, whale watching, and more. Enjoy the scenery of Lovers Beach, Santa Maria Bay, and enjoy the Sea of Cortez that Jacque Cousteau nicknamed “The Aquarium of the World” all are waiting for you with s customized tour.

Whale Shark Encounter in La Paz.
Enjoy an outstanding ALL-INCLUSIVE cruise, on a large and spacious sailing catamaran, and snorkel with the largest fish in the world!
The whale shark filters surface water for microscopic plankton, which allows us to swim beside these rare and gentle giants. Baja Whale sharks are the premier tour of its kind, their all-inclusive whale shark excursion includes a cruise of approximately 4.5 to 5 hours, and includes savory chef-prepared meals, a skilled and educated crew, and a marine biologist as snorkel leader. We provide a powered support boat, bottled water, beer, sodas, an open bar, private bathrooms, fresh water showers, laundered towels, all the equipment, even reef-friendly sunscreen. We are NOT a cattle-car Tour operator. Truly a lifetime experience

Go Extreme Off-road with Wide Open Baja.
This is the ultimate off-road experience that is for the adrenaline-seeking adventurer. This is their full-day program from 8-10 hours you will travel across an array of Baja sceneries in a Baja Race Car. Be guided by experienced Baja racers and discover the hidden beauty of Los Cabos. You will discover one of the true challenges of extreme off-road travel.

Diving snd snorkeling tours in Cabo Pulmo Marine Park.
The village of Cabo Pulmo was established in 1987 and currently has a population of 114, the National Marine Park of Cabo Pulmo was established in 1995 to protect the oldest living Coral Reef in North America. Cabo Pulmo Dive Resort welcomes you to what is quickly becoming the biggest nature conservation success story in all of North America.
On the water, in the water or on land the natural beauty of Cabo Pulmo is a little piece of paradise. You will never forget having a local tour guide introduce you to the many popular marine sites. Their guides speak English & Spanish. 
Snorkeling and diving for age groups 8 and older. Treat yourself to a world-class marine sanctuary experience.   Their divemasters & instructors are PADI certified to introduce you to the many favorite marine sites.

Luxury Whale Watching Cruise with Cabo Adventures.
When it comes to spotting whales, Cabo San Lucas is a worldwide hotspot. That’s because the waters surrounding Cabo are breeding areas and migratory stops for whales in the Pacific Ocean. To help you get as close to these magnificent creatures as possible and take pictures the experts at Cabo Adventures proudly offer this one-of-a-kind luxury whale watching tour...
